\begin{center}
{\Large\bf The Maillet--Malgrange type theorem for generalized power series}
\end{center}

\begin{center}
\large \bf R.\,R.\,Gontsov, I.\,V.\,Goryuchkina
\end{center}
\bigskip

\begin{abstract}
There is proposed the Maillet--Malgrange type theorem for a generalized power series (having complex power exponents) 
formally satisfying an algebraic ordinary differential equation. The theorem describes the growth of the series coefficients.  
\end{abstract}

\section{Introduction} 

Let us consider an ordinary differential equation (ODE) 
\begin{eqnarray}\label{ADE}
